**Debt‑to‑Asset Ratio (2024)**  

\[
\text{Debt‑to‑Asset Ratio}= \frac{\text{Total Debt}}{\text{Total Assets}}
= \frac{\text{TOTAL LIABILITIES}}{\text{TOTAL EQUITY AND LIABILITIES}}
= \frac{368\,171\,788}{476\,288\,765}
\approx 0.7730
\]

**Result:** **0.773 (≈ 77.3 %)** – unit‑less ratio, expressed as a percentage if desired.

**Average Accounts Receivable**

\[
\frac{\text{Trade receivables 2024} + \text{Trade receivables 2023}}{2}
= \frac{2\,164\,840\ \text{EUR} + 1\,606\,770\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= \frac{3\,771\,610\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= 1\,885\,805\ \text{EUR}
\]

**Result:** **€ 1,885,805**.

**Days Sales Outstanding (DSO)**  

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{\text{Average Accounts Receivable}\times 365}{\text{Revenue}}
\]

- **Trade receivables (31 Dec 2024)** = 2 164 840 EUR  
- **Trade receivables (31 Dec 2023)** = 1 606 770 EUR  

\[
\text{Average Accounts Receivable}= \frac{2 164 840 + 1 606 770}{2}=1 885 805\ \text{EUR}
\]

- **Revenue for 2024** (from Table 3, “Revenue, 12M 2024”) = 371.2 million EUR = 371 200 000 EUR  

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{1 885 805 \times 365}{371 200 000}
           \approx \frac{688 318 825}{371 200 000}
           \approx 1.85\ \text{days}
\]

**Result:** **≈ 1.9 days** (rounded to one decimal place).

**Average Net Fixed Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Net Fixed Assets}_{2024} + \text{Net Fixed Assets}_{2023}}{2}
= \frac{16\,282\,205\ \text{EUR} + 20\,517\,356\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= \frac{36\,799\,561\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= 18\,399\,780.5\ \text{EUR}
\]

**Result:** **≈ 18,399,781 EUR** (rounded to the nearest euro).

**Average Total Assets**  

\[
\frac{\text{Total Assets 2024} + \text{Total Assets 2023}}{2}
= \frac{476{,}288{,}765\ \text{EUR} + 421{,}315{,}533\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= \frac{897{,}604{,}298\ \text{EUR}}{2}
= 448{,}802{,}149\ \text{EUR}
\]

**Result:** **448,802,149 EUR**.
